apoc.generate.relationship

Class BarabasiAlbertRelationshipGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • apoc.generate.relationship.BaseRelationshipGenerator<BarabasiAlbertConfig>
      • apoc.generate.relationship.BarabasiAlbertRelationshipGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RelationshipGenerator

    public class BarabasiAlbertRelationshipGenerator
extends BaseRelationshipGenerator<BarabasiAlbertConfig>
    RelationshipGenerator implemented according to the Barabasi-Albert preferential attachment model, which is appropriate for networks reflecting cumulative advantage (rich get richer).

    Each newly added node has a probability weighted by the node degree to be attached. Since BA references (Newmann, Barabasi-Albert) do not define strict conditions on initial state of the model, completely connected network is used to start up the algorithm.
